            <div class="container" style="background-color:#d9e8cf;padding:20px;">
                <p>Dear Merchant,</p>
                <p>
                    
                    We are offering "<b>Lazypay Services</b>" under the Service Agreement which you have with PayU. With this option, you can enable your customers to make payment using deferred 
                    payment facility to be provided by you using buy now pay later technology and also avail credit services as may be provided through NBFC, as a part of Lazypay Services.
                    The details of the services are mentioned in the addendum below.</p><p>
                Once you accept this Addendum by clicking on ‘<b>Accept</b>’, we shall enable the feature for your account.</p><p>
                In case you want to understand further features of Lazypay Services or do not wish to continue with Lazypay Services, please write to us at <a>newstuff@payu.in</a> and we will be happy to assist. 
                </p><p>Thank You.</p>
                
                
            </div>
            <div class="container">
                <!--<h3  class="center-text"><u style="align:center!important;">ADDENDUM</u></h3>-->
                <p align="center">
                    <STRONG><u>LAZYPAY ADDENDUM</u></STRONG>
                </p>
                <p>This addendum
                    <STRONG>("Addendum")</STRONG> is made at <strong>New Delhi</strong> on<strong>&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0, date, d MMMM','  yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!TODAY()}" /></apex:outputText></strong> <strong>("Effective Date")</strong> by and between:</p>
                
                
                <p><strong>PayU Payments Private Limited,</strong> a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956 having its registered office at 2nd Floor, P&amp;G Plaza Cardinal Gracious Road, Chakala, Andheri (East) Mumbai, Mumbai City, Maharashtra, Pin-400099 and corporate office at 9th Floor, Bestech Business Tower, Sector 48, Sohna Road, Gurgaon, Haryana, Pin - 122002 (hereinafter referred to as <strong>"PayU"</strong>, which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context thereof, include its successors-in-interest and assigns) of First part;</p>
                <p><strong>AND</strong></p>
                <p><strong>{!accObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong>, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956/2013 having its registered office at 
                    <strong>{!IF(regAddress.Address_Line__c!=null,regAddress.Address_Line__c, null)}
                        {!IF(regParentAddress.City__c!=null, ', '+regParentAddress.City__c, null)}
                        {!IF(regParentAddress.State__c!=null, ', '+regParentAddress.State__c, null)}
                        {!IF(regParentAddress.Country__c!=null, ', '+regParentAddress.Country__c, null)}
                        {!IF(regAddress.Pincode__c!=null, ', '+regAddress.Pincode__c,null)}
                    </strong> 
                    (hereinafter referred to as <strong>“Merchant”</strong> which expression shall, unless repugnant to the context thereof, include its successors and permitted assigns) of the Second part;</p>
                <p>PayU and the Merchant are hereinafter collectively referred to as <strong>"Parties"</strong> and individually as <strong>"Party"</strong>. </p>
                <p><strong>WHEREAS:</strong></p>
                <table cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse: collapse;">
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">A.</td>
                        <td>The Parties have entered into a Service Agreement (hereinafter referred to as <strong>“Service Agreement”</strong>) in accordance to which PayU provides the Merchant with PayU Services for the Merchant Site.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">B.</td>
                        <td>The Merchant is further desirous of offering its Customers an option to make payment using buy now pay later technology and credit services extended by Paysense Consultancy Services India Private Limited under the brand name ‘Lazypay’ (<strong>“Lazypay Services”</strong>).</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">C.</td>
                        <td >PayU has agreed to provide Lazypay Services to the Merchant and the Merchant has agreed to avail the same on the terms and conditions hereinafter contained in this Addendum. </td>   
                    </tr>
                    <br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top"></td>
                        <td>In consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein and for other good, valuable and binding consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, the Parties agree to the following amendments:</td>
                    </tr>
                    <br/>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign = "top"><strong>1</strong>.</td>
                        <td><strong>DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">1.1</td>
                        <td>For the purpose of this Addendum, unless the context requires otherwise, the following terms and conditions shall have the meaning defined below. The terms capitalized and not defined under this Addendum shall have the same meaning ascribed to them under the Service Agreement:.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">a)</td>
                        <td><strong>“BNPL Customer(s)”</strong> shall mean a customer(s) of the Merchant who is an individual purchasing Product(s) from the Merchant: (a) for whom the BNPL Option has been authorized by the Merchant and (b) who has utilized or agrees to utilize the BNPL Option to undertake one or more BNPL Transaction;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">b)</td>
                        <td><strong>“BNPL Option”</strong> shall mean a technology enabled solution, provided by the Facility Provider to the Merchant, enabling the Merchant to offer a deferred payment option in the nature of buy-now-pay-later to certain of its identified customers buying Products from the Merchant and as made available by the Merchant to its Customers using Technology Enabled Settlement Services provided Facility;</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">c)</td>
                        <td><strong>“BNPL Payment Period”</strong> shall have the meaning assigned to it under clause 3.4;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">d)</td>
                        <td><strong>"BNPL Settlement Amount(s)"</strong> shall mean the amount equivalent to BNPL Transaction Amount minus (i) the Service Fee payable by the Merchant for availing Technology Enabled Settlement Services; and (ii) anyother deduction agreed under the Addendum or the Service Agreement, collected by the Facility Provider from the BNPL Customer in accordance with the terms and conditions agreed with the BNPL Customer within the BNPL Payment Period;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">e)</td>
                        <td><strong>"BNPL Transaction(s)"</strong> shall mean a transaction for the purchase of Product(s) made by a BNPL Customer on the Merchant Site, for which the BNPL Option has been authorized by the Merchant and the BNPL Customer has availed such BNPL Option;</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">f)</td>
                        <td><strong>"BNPL Transaction Amount(s)"</strong> shall mean the amount required to be paid by a BNPL Customer for the purchase of Product(s) on the Merchant Site of the Merchant and for which the BNPL Option is exercised by such BNPL Customer;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">g)</td>
                        <td><strong>"Credit Line Customer(s)"</strong> shall mean a customer(s) who is an individual purchasing Product(s) utilizing or drawing down any credit line that has been made available to such customer by a Partner Financial Institution;</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">h)</td>
                        <td><strong>"Credit Line Settlement Amount(s)"</strong> shall mean any amount equivalent to Credit Line Transaction Amount minus (i) the Service Fee payable by the Merchant to PayU for availing Settlement Processing Services; and (ii) anyother deduction agreed under the Addendum or Service Agreement, provided in form of credit facility by the Facility Provider to the Credit Line Customer in accordance with the terms and conditions agreed with the Credit Line Customer;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">i)</td>
                        <td><strong>"Credit Line Transaction(s)"</strong> means a transaction for purchase of Product(s) made by a Credit Line Customer for which such Credit Line Customer has utilized or drawn down any credit line from a Partner Financial Institution;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">j)</td>
                        <td><strong>"Credit Line T  ransaction Amount(s)"</strong> shall mean the amount required to be paid by a Credit Line Customer for purchasing Product(s) and for which such Credit Line Customer has utilized or drawn down any credit line that has been made available to such Credit Line Customer by the Partner Financial Institution;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">k)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Effective Date”</strong> shall mean the date when this Addendum comes into force which, in this case, is the date of execution of this Addendum as stated hereinabove;</td>
                        
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">l)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Facility”</strong> shall mean the Technology Enabled Settlement Services and Settlement Processing Services provided by the Facility Provider;</td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">m)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Facility Provider”</strong> shall mean Paysense or anyother entity providing the Facility. The term Facility Provider shall be deemed to be included in the definition of the Acquiring Bank, to the extent applicable.</td>  
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">n)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Lazypay Platform”</strong> means the proprietary technology platform named “LazyPay” for which Paysense holds a valid license granted by the proprietor entity for the limited purpose of providing a dashboard to any BNPL Customer and which can be used by such BNPL Customer for tracking and managing BNPL Transactions in accordance with the terms and conditions agreed between such BNPL Customers and the Facility Provider;</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">o)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Outstanding Amounts”</strong> shall mean amounts payable by the Merchant to PayU and/ or Facility Provider in accordance with the terms of this Addendum and shall include, without limitation, any amounts relating to any financial liability, losses, costs, damages, penalties, suffered or incurred Facility, directly or indirectly, in connection with or arising from: (i) any chargebacks, non-delivery of Product(s), supply of defective Product(s), refunds, cash backs, or any other payments or liability owed by the Merchant to BNPL Customers or Credit Line Customers, (ii) any claims or proceedings filed against PayU and/ or Facility Provider by any BNPL Customer(s) or Credit Line Customer(s) or any third Party, and (iii) any failure of a Customer to pay any BNPL Transaction Amount or to repay a Credit Line Transaction Amount due to a cause or reason attributable to any Product(s) supplied by the Merchant. This definition shall be in addition to the definition of Outstanding Amount under the Service Agreement;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">p)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Partner Financial Institution”</strong> shall mean a bank or a financial institution who has authorized the Facility Provider to offer Settlement Processing Services to the Merchant on its behalf in order to enable its customers to make the payment using or drawing down a credit line from the bank;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">q)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Performance Assurance Deposit”</strong> shall have the same meaning ascribed to it under Clause 3.3.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">r)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Settlement Processing Services”</strong> shall have the meaning assigned to it under clause 2.1(b);</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">s)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Statement”</strong> shall have the meaning assigned to it under Clause 5.1;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">t)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Technology Enabled Settlement Services”</strong> shall have the meaning assigned to it under clause 2.1(a);</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">u)</td>
                        <td><strong>“Transaction”</strong> shall collectively mean both BNPL Transaction and Credit Line Transaction; and</td>
                    </tr>
                    <br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top"><b>2.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>SCOPE OF FACILITY</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">2.1</td>
                        <td>For the purpose of this Addendum, Facility shall mean and include Technology Enabled Settlement Services and Settlement Processing Services as described below:</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">a)</td>
                        <td><strong>Technology Enabled Settlement Services</strong>, shall mean and consist of technology services, customer identification services and collection services provided as a part of Facility to the Merchant, through which the Merchant is enabled to: (i) authorize BNPL Options for BNPL Customers for the purposes of purchase of Product(s) on the Merchant Site and (ii) receiving the BNPL Settlement Amounts against BNPL Transactions, in the manner as contemplated in this Addendum in relation to BNPL Transactions made by BNPL Customers on the Merchant Site; and</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">b)</td>
                        <td><strong>Settlement Processing Services</strong>, shall mean and consist of technology services and settlement services provided as a part of Facility to the Merchant enabling the Merchant to: (i) offer its customers an option to make payment towards Credit Line Transactions for purchase of Product(s) and (ii) receive Credit Line Settlement Amounts in relation to Credit Line Transactions made by Credit Line Customers on the Merchant Site.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <br/><br/>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><b>3.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>PROCESS FLOW AND SETTLEMENT FOR TECHNOLGY ENABLED SETTLEMENT SERVICES</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.1</td>
                        <td>As a part of Technology Enabled Settlement Services provided as a part of Facility, a technology enabled solution will be made available to the Merchant which will enable the Merchant to identify and authorize the BNPL Option for its customers from amongst the customer base of the Merchant.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.2</td>
                        <td>Once a customer of the Merchant opts for the BNPL Option and successfully completes a BNPL Transaction on or through the Merchant Site, subject to receipt of the BNPL Settlement Amount by PayU from the Facility Provider and the provisions of the Service Agreement and Addendum, PayU will: (i) remit the applicable BNPL Settlement Amount to the Client in the manner agreed under this Addendum and (ii) collect the BNPL Transaction Amount from the BNPL Customer on behalf of the Merchant, in accordance with the terms and conditions agreed by the BNPL Customer with the Facility Provider.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.3</td>
                        <td>The Merchant hereby irrevocably and unconditionally authorizes and permits the Facility Provider, on its behalf, to: (a) collect the BNPL Transaction Amount from the relevant BNPL Customer on behalf of the Merchant, as the case may be, in the manner and within the timelines agreed by the BNPL Customer while opting to pay through the BNPL Option, (b) settle the BNPL Settlement Amount to the Merchant and (c) set-off any BNPL Transaction Amount collected from BNPL Customers where any BNPL Settlement Amounts have already been made available by the Facility Provider to the Merchant as Performance Assurance Deposit in the manner as described in this Addendum. ("<strong>Performance Assurance Deposit</strong>”)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.4</td>
                        <td>For any BNPL Transaction(s) processed as a part of Technology Enabled Settlement Services, the Facility Provider may, in its discretion and as a measure of performance assurance, maintain a Performance Assurance Deposit with the Merchant approximately equivalent to BNPL Settlement Amount due to be settled by the Facility provider for each BNPL Transaction taking place on any particular day. Subject to other provisions of this Addendum and the Service Agreement, the Performance Assurance Deposit with respect to a BNPL Transaction processed on a particular day shall be made available by Facility Provider within 2 Business Days of the BNPL Transaction taking place. The Facility Provider shall maintain the Performance Assurance Deposit in the Merchant Bank Account. Any amount maintained as Performance Assurance Deposit by Facility Provider shall be set-off against any BNPL Settlement Amounts payable by the Facility Provider to the Client in accordance with the terms of this Service Agreement.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.5</td>
                        <td>The maintenance of the Performance Assurance Deposit and/or the settlement of any BNPL Settlement Amounts  by the Facility Provider and/ or PayU against any BNPL Transactions shall be on a non-recourse basis subject to: (i) the absolute liability of the Merchant for any disputes or liabilities of the Merchant(s) with BNPL Customers in relation to any Product(s), and (ii) any claims or disputes raised by BNPL Customers with regard to the above or any failure of or delay by BNPL Customers to pay the BNPL Transaction Amount(s) to the Facility Provider for reasons attributable to the Client and/ or Merchant, and such amounts shall form part of the Outstanding Amounts.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.6</td>
                        <td>BNPL Customers shall be required to make payments as per the timelines agreed between such BNPL Customers and Facility Provider in relation to any BNPL Transaction (“<strong>BNPL Payment Period</strong>”). </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">3.7</td>
                        <td>The Facility Provider shall, as a part of Technology Enabled Settlement Services, evaluate and identify to the Merchant, customers of the Merchant who can potentially be authorized by the Merchant to exercise the BNPL Option. Such evaluation and identification of customers shall be done by the Facility Provider on the basis of: (i) the customer database shared by the Merchant, and/ or (ii) from the database available with Facility Provider including any third party databases or data from other banks and financial institutions.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <br/><br/><br/><br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top"><b>4.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>PROCESS FLOW AND SETTLEMENT FOR SETTLEMENT PROCESSING SERVICES</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">4.1</td>
                        <td>As a part of Settlement Processing Services provided as a part of Facility, a technology enabled solution will be made available to the Merchant, using which customers of the Merchant will be able to carry out Credit Line Transaction(s) through Partner Financial Institutions.</td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">4.2</td>
                        <td>Once a customer of the Merchant successfully completes a Credit Line Transaction on the Merchant Site, subject to the provisions of this Addendum and Service Agreement, PayU shall subject to receipt of funds from the Facility Provider, remit the applicable Credit Line Settlement Amount to the Merchant which shall be equivalent to an amount that is the Credit Line Transaction Amount minus the Service Fee (TDR) chargeable by PayU, within 3 (three) Business Days from the date of the Credit Line Transaction. PayU shall settle the Credit Line Transaction Amount as Settlement Amount to the Merchant Bank Account.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top">4.3</td>
                        <td>The settlement of Credit Line Settlement Amounts Facility to the Merchant against any Credit Line Transactions shall be subject to: (i) the absolute liability of the Merchant for any disputes or liabilities with Credit Line Customers in relation to any Product(s), and (ii) any claims or disputes raised by Credit Line Customers with regard to the above or any failure of or delay by Credit Line Customers to pay the Credit Line Transaction Amount(s) to the Partner Financial Institution.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top"><b>5.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>LAZYPAY PLATFORM AND STATEMENTS</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">5.1</td>
                        <td>Facility Provider may provide a statement periodically to each BNPL Customer of the Merchant pertaining to BNPL Transactions undertaken by such BNPL Customer in the preceding 2 (Two) weeks or such other time period as may be agreed with the BNPL Customer from time to time, specifying details pertaining to the timelines and manner in which BNPL Transaction Amounts are required to be paid by that BNPL Customer (<strong>“Statement”</strong>), by e-mail or SMS or any other medium including a web or mobile platform as identified by the Facility Provider from time to time. This Statement will be a consolidated statement containing the transactions which the customer has completed with other merchants using the Facility provided by the Facility Provider.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">5.2</td>
                        <td>The Facility Provider may also include in the Statement any particulars or details of any Credit Line Transactions conducted by a Credit Line Customer who is or has been a BNPL Customer, specifying details pertaining to the timelines and manner in which Credit Line Transaction Amounts are required to be paid by that Credit Line Customer. The Facility Provider may also share a consolidated Statement for the BNPL Transactions and Credit Line Transactions.</td> 
                        
                        
                    </tr>
                    <br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top"><b>6.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS OF THE PARTIES</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">6.1</td>
                        <td>In relation to Facility, the Merchant hereby irrevocably and unconditionally agrees as follows:</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">a)</td>
                        <td>as a part of the Technology Enabled Settlement Services, hereby authorizes the Facility Provider to accept payments of BNPL Transaction Amounts from BNPL Customers, for and on behalf of the Merchant;</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">b)</td>
                        <td>set-off BNPL Transaction Amounts and Credit Line Transaction Amounts collected from BNPL Customers and Credit Line Customers against any amounts owed by the Merchant to PayU and the Facility Provider on account of Facility or otherwise in accordance with the terms of the Service Agreement and Addendum;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">c)</td>
                        <td>levy such charges and late payment fee as may be agreed with the BNPL Customers, on behalf of the Merchant, in case of failure of a BNPL Customer to pay the BNPL Transaction Amount within the BNPL Payment Period and retain such amounts;</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <br/><br/><br/><br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">d)</td>
                        <td>create and implement a framework and complaints resolution mechanism, binding on the Merchant and any BNPL Customers and/or Credit Line Customers, to address grievances of BNPL Customers and Credit Line Customers in relation to any BNPL Transactions or Credit Line Transactions or Products purchased by such BNPL Customers or Credit Line Customers. Any such framework and complaints resolution mechanism created or implemented by the Facility Provider may include, at Facility Provider’s discretion, calling upon the Merchant, BNPL Customer and/ or Credit Line Customer to provide relevant information and documents as the Facility Provider may deem necessary and decision of the Facility Provider in relation to such disputes shall be final and binding on the Merchant, BNPL Customer and/or Credit Line Customer; and</td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td valign = "top">e)</td>
                        <td>Merchant agrees that that in order to make payments using BNPL Option, BNPL Customers and Credit Line Customers, as applicable, will have to accept terms and conditions provided on the LazyPay platform. The Merchant further agrees that the records generated the Facility Provider while providing Facility shall be owned by PayU and the Facility Provider and can be used by them in accordance with applicable laws. For collection and usage of any data from any BNPL Customers and any Credit Line Customers, as necessary, Facility Provider may additionally seek rights directly from such Customers in accordance with applicable laws. In addition, the Facility Provider will share records and data in relation to Customers with the Partner Financial Institutions and other banks or financial institutions on whose behalf Facility Provider may be acting.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">6.2</td>
                        <td>The Parties hereby, mutually, unconditionally and irrevocably, agree, understand and covenant as under:</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">a)</td>
                        <td>The Merchant agrees that in the event of any defaulting BNPL Customer(s) or Credit Line Customer(s), the Facility Provider and/or its Partner Financial Institutions, shall be authorized to block such defaulting BNPL Customers or Credit Line Customers. In addition, the Facility Provider and/or its Partner Financial Institutions, shall have the unconditional right to not allow BNPL Customers or Credit Line Customers to carry out a BNPL Transaction or a Credit Line Transaction where they have reasons to believe that such BNPL Transactions or Credit Line Transactions are not authorized or the same do not appear to be genuine or clear or for any other reasonable reasons as may be deemed fit Facility and/or its Partner Financial Institutions. Processing of a Credit Line Transaction shall be at the sole discretion of the Facility provider and/or of its Partner Financial Institutions.</td>   
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">b)</td>
                        <td>The Parties hereby agree that PayU, the Facility Provider and/or Partner Financial Institutions, as applicable, will have the right to withhold and/ or suspend any transaction and/ or settlement, in the event of breach of terms of the Service Agreement and/ or Addendum, fraudulent acts or misrepresentations including suspicion of such breach, fraudulent acts or misrepresentation on the part of the Merchant or any Customers or any third party, any delivery issues or complaints and/ or chargebacks in relation to the Products supplied by the Merchant.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">c)</td>
                        <td>The Parties agree that the Facility are to be provided solely at the discretion of Facility Provider and PayU and the Facility Provider and PayU retains the right to modify and/ or discontinue the same, in part or as a whole, or deny the provision of Facility to the Merchant. PayU shall endeavor to intimate the Merchant of such modification and/ or discontinuity and/ or denial.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">d)</td>
                        <td>The Parties hereby agree that the Merchant shall provide all support and cooperation to PayU and Facility Provider and/or its affiliate companies and/or its Partner Financial Institutions, in collecting BNPL Transaction Amounts and Credit Line Transaction Amounts including providing all necessary information about any BNPL Transactions and Credit Line Transactions.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <br/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">e)</td>
                        <td>The Parties hereby agree that the Facility Provider and/ or the Partner Financial Institution, and their personnel or auditors (internal or external) or legal advisors and regulators/ government authorities (including, without limitation, the RBI or persons authorized by RBI) shall have the right to inspect and/or audit all records of the Merchant, that relate to the arrangements contemplated in this Addendum and Service Agreement and the Merchant shall facilitate such inspection and/or audit promptly and in good faith.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top"><b>7.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>CONSIDERATION AND SETTLEMENT OF ACCOUNTS</strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top">7.1</td>
                        <td>In consideration of Facility rendered in accordance with the terms of this Addendum, the Merchant agrees to pay to PayU the non-refundable Service Fee (TDR) as detailed in <strong>Pricing Schedule – Schedule - B</strong> in relation to each BNPL Transaction and each Credit Line Transaction.</td> 
                    </tr>
                    <br/>
                    <tr>
                        
                        <td valign = "top"><b>8.</b></td>
                        <td><strong>COMPLAINTS RESOLUTION MECHANISM</strong></td>
                    </tr>
